The paper deals with network traffic analysis and security, which are topics typically covered in the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) sub-categories. The use of Poisson processes and M/M/1 queues suggests a focus on mathematical modeling and analysis, which could place the paper in the cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-categories. Finally, the paper's discussion of network models and extensions could also make it relevant to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category.
